<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="118" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="39" pageNumber="118">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="39" pageNumber="118">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Agaricostilbomycetes" family="Chrysididae" genus="Stilbum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stilbum westermanni" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="118" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="westermanni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="118">Stilbum westermanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is related to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1781" class="Agaricostilbomycetes" family="Chrysididae" genus="Stilbum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stilbum calens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="118" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="calens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="118">Stilbum calens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fabricius. 
<bibRefCitation author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Entomofauna" pageId="45" pageNumber="124" pagination="245 - 300" refId="B48" refString="Linsenmaier, W, 1997a. Altes und Neues von den Chrysididen (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae). Entomofauna 18 (19): 245 - 300" title="Altes und Neues von den Chrysididen (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae)." volume="18" year="1997 a">Linsenmaier (1997a</bibRefCitation>
: 287, 
<bibRefCitation author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Veroffentlichungen aus dem Natur-Museum Luzer" pageId="45" pageNumber="124" refId="B49" refString="Linsenmaier, W, 1997b. Die Goldwespen der Schweiz. Veroffentlichungen aus dem Natur-Museum Luzer 9" title="Die Goldwespen der Schweiz." volume="9" year="1997 b">1997b</bibRefCitation>
: 134, 
<bibRefCitation author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Veroffentlichungen aus dem Natur-Museum Luzer" pageId="45" pageNumber="124" refId="B50" refString="Linsenmaier, W, 1999. Die Goldwespen Nordafrikas (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae). In: Entomofauna." title="Die Goldwespen Nordafrikas (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae)." volumeTitle="Entomofauna." year="1999">1999</bibRefCitation>
: 254) confused the two species described by Dahlbom from Rhodes (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="118">wesmaeli</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="118">westermanni</emphasis>
), and proposed the wrong combination 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Agaricostilbomycetes" family="Chrysididae" genus="Stilbum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stilbum calens subsp. wesmaeli" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="118" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="subSpecies" species="calens" subSpecies="wesmaeli">Stilbum calens ssp. wesmaeli</taxonomicName>
instead of 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricostilbomycetes" family="Chrysididae" genus="Stilbum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stilbum calens subsp. westermanni" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="118" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="subSpecies" species="calens" subSpecies="westermanni">Stilbum calens ssp. westermanni</taxonomicName>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Linsenmaier, W" journalOrPublisher="Veroffentlichungen aus dem Natur-Museum Luzer" pageId="45" pageNumber="124" refId="B49" refString="Linsenmaier, W, 1997b. Die Goldwespen der Schweiz. Veroffentlichungen aus dem Natur-Museum Luzer 9" title="Die Goldwespen der Schweiz." volume="9" year="1997 b">Linsenmaier (1997b)</bibRefCitation>
, this subspecies is more distributed along the coast of the Mediterranean basin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
